LakeVille Middle School, Otisville, MI
September 10 at 3:37 PM ¬∑

Middle school sports will be starting soon. Football, cheerleading and girls basketball will begin as soon as next week. In order to tryout/practice students must have a physical on file and also have their emergency and responsibility form filled out and turned into office. Fees must be paid prior to first game. Fees are determined according to free/reduced lunch. Virtual students are allowed and welcome to play on teams. If you need the forms please contact the middle school office and we will get those to you. Football is 8th grade, 7th graders playing youth football may be used if we need more players. Cheerleading and girls basketball are open to 6,7 and 8th graders. If you have questions please contact the office. 810-591-3945

NATIONAL NEWS ALERT!
The Graphics CommunicationWorkforce Coalition (GCWC) just announced that Brianna (Brie) Macsuga, a GCI Visual Digital Communications has won first place in their national logo contest. Graphic Communications Workforce Coalition (GCWC) is comprised of several graphics related company members who represent a ‚Äúspectrum‚Äù of the graphics and printing industries and are focused on growing a strong graphic arts workforce. The GCWC opened the contest in February 2020 and the board chose her design this week. Her design as well as two other students were uploaded during our stay at home order. Brie‚Äôs entry was chosen by the board from entries from across the country and she will be awarded a $1000 scholarship for this win! Another bright shining GCI CTE star- Congratulations to LakeVille‚Äôs Brianna Macsuga!

shared_text:
LakeVille Community Schools
April 1 at 12:32 PM ¬∑

Hospital Supply Drive!

Local Hospitals have reached out to local school districts for donations and help collecting supplies.

Are you home on quarantine wondering what you might be able to do to help? Do you have some buyers remorse when you over purchased cleaning supplies and toilet paper during this unstable time? Do you have a couple bottles of hand sanitizer, clorox type wipes, safety glasses, face masks, and/or rubber gloves that you might be able to spare for our medical professionals on the front line helping to fight this Virus?

Well, If you said yes to any of the above, we will gladly collect what you have have available (minus the toilet paper), no matter the quantity. We will have a drive-up drop off collection site set up at the Middle School this Friday and this Friday only from 10-12. Once all items are collected, they will be delivered to Hurley Hospital on Behalf of LakeVille Community Schools.

Let's do our part to help those helping us!

#FalconPride

Are you home on quarantine wondering what you might be able to do to help? Do you have some buyers remorse when you over purchased cleaning supplies and toilet paper during this unstable time? Do you have a couple bottles of hand sanitizer, clorox type wipes, safety glasses, face masks, and/or rubber gloves that you might be able to spare for our medical professionals on the front line helping to fight this Virus?

Well, If you said yes to any of the above, we will gladly collect what you have have available (minus the toilet paper), no matter the quantity. We will have a drive-up drop off collection site set up at the Middle School this Friday and this Friday only from 10-12. Once all items are collected, they will be delivered to Hurley Hospital on Behalf of LakeVille Community Schools.

Let's do our part to help those helping us!

#FalconPride

post_text:
Good Afternoon Falcon Families,

I hope this message finds you healthy and well.

I wanted to address an article that was released by Bridge Magazine earlier this week. The article left us all with more questions than answers at this time. Though my gut says most of these items will become reality later this week when/if the Governor signs an executive order putting them into action, the information in the article is to be considered an opinion of the journalist.:

https://www.bridgemi.com/talent-education/whitmer-end-michigan-school-year-seniors-graduate-others-move

Once we have additional information and direction from the state, district leaders will be working to make the recommended changes. Until then, we will continue to provide learning opportunities and resources for you and your family.

Please continue to be patient, flexible and supportive.

Stay home, stay safe, and wash your hands!

Mike Lytle
Superintendent

post_text:
Good Morning Falcon Families,

We have been asked by the Michigan Department of Education (MDE) to collect data in our district about access to technology and the internet. We will be sending out an automated phone survey around 3:00 today to families of current students. The survey has only three quick questions. Please plan to respond to this call. The survey should only be taken once for each household.

The MDE will be looking at this data to help determine and assist districts with online learning opportunities should our closure be extended. Though that has not been determined at this time, more importantly this information will help us to better meet the needs of our students and support our families.

Again, please plan to respond to the phone survey this afternoon. Also please share this message with families who might not see it here on Facebook.

Stay Home. Stay Safe!

#FalconPride

With the Governor‚Äôs announcement this evening, LakeVille Community Schools will be closed beginning tomorrow, Friday, March 13, 2020 through April 5, 2020. School will resume Monday, April 6, 2020.

Due to the late notice, kids club will be open tomorrow, however, families will need to look for other options of daycare moving forward.

Only Administrative, custodial/maintenance and secretarial staff to report tomorrow.

We ask that you please be patient, supportive and flexible during these difficult and unprecedented times. We will continue to update as additional information becomes available.
